{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "hashrate_2016_verification",
    "description": "Verify that hashrate_split non-causality holds at 2016-block retarget conditions.\nAt 144-block retarget (targeted_sweep2_hashrate_economic, 42 scenarios), hashrate_split was shown to have zero effect on fork outcomes when pool_committed_split is fixed at 0.50 (above the Foundry flip-point ~0.214). Economic split dominated regardless of hashrate. However, that finding was validated only at 144-block retarget on a full 60-node network.\nThe 2016-block regime is qualitatively different: the minority chain suffers a much longer difficulty penalty period (~67 min per retarget vs ~5 min), which could amplify the hashrate signal. Specifically, a larger hashrate advantage on v26 means a more severe minority-chain fee squeeze over a much longer window before the retarget cascade fires. This sweep tests whether hashrate_split changes the decision boundary at 2016-block or remains non-causal as assumed in the Phase 2 PRIM analysis.\nDESIGN:\n  - pool_committed_split fixed at 0.35 (above Foundry flip-point, near transition zone boundary)\n  - economic_split sampled at 3 levels spanning the transition zone (0.50, 0.60, 0.70)\n  - hashrate_split swept across 6 levels (0.15 \u2192 heavy v26 advantage, 0.65 \u2192 near parity)\n  - Grid: 6 hashrate \u00d7 3 economic = 18 scenarios\n  - Full 60-node network (required: economic_split must vary across nodes, not quantize)\n\nEXPECTED OUTCOME (if non-causality holds):\n  - Each economic_split column should produce the same outcome across all 6 hashrate rows\n  - If hashrate_split IS causal: some hashrate values will flip outcome within an econ column\n\nNOTE ON PRIOR RUN (2026-03-22):\n  The first run of this sweep used lite network + pool_committed_split=0.50 (mirroring\n  targeted_sweep2). All 18 scenarios returned v27_dominant (86.4%) \u2014 confirming\n  non-causality, but economic_split did not vary due to lite network quantization.\n  This rebuild uses full 60-node network and pool_committed_split=0.35 (closer to the\n  transition boundary, providing a more demanding test) with corrected parameters.\n\nVALIDATED PARAMS: Uses corrected econ switching parameters (threshold=0.10, inertia=0.05) matching all v2 sweeps.\nRUNTIME: 18 scenarios \u00d7 ~13,000s = ~234,000s total. On full network at ~90 min/scenario: ~27h sequential. Recommended: 6 namespaces \u00d7 3 scenarios each \u2192 ~4.5h wall-clock (parallel).\nRun command:\n  python tools/sweep/1_generate_targeted.py --spec specs/hashrate_2016_verification.yaml\n  python tools/sweep/2_build_configs.py \\\n    --input hashrate_2016_verification/scenarios.json \\\n    --output-dir hashrate_2016_verification\n  python tools/sweep/3_run_sweep.py \\\n    --input hashrate_2016_verification/build_manifest.json \\\n    --results-dir hashrate_2016_verification/results \\\n    --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2\n",
    "spec_file": "specs/hashrate_2016_verification.yaml",
